# {{uncountable}} The ability to communicate using words.
#: ''the gift of '''language'''''
# {{context|countable|or|uncountable}} Nonverbal communication.
#: ''body '''language'''''
# {{context|computing|countable}} A [[computer language]].
# {{uncountable}} The [[vocabulary]] and [[usage]] used in a particular [[specialist]] field.
#: ''legal '''language'''''
# {{uncountable}} The particular words used in speech or a passage of text.
#: ''The '''language''' he used to talk to me was obscene.''
#: ''The '''language''' used in the law does not permit any other interpretation.''
# {{uncountable}} [[profanity|Profanity]].
#* {{quote-book
|page=500
|year=1978
|author=James Carroll
|title=Mortal Friends
|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Nbl6vw3uieoC
|isbn=0440157897
|passage="Where the hell is Horace?" ¶"There he is.  He's coming.  You shouldn't use '''language'''."}}
# Words, written or spoken, in a specific sequence that a person uses to describe, to a another person, the type of thoughts in their mind.

